## Section-by-Section Design (Adapting tajmirul.site → Ahmed Moosani)

### 1. Custom Cursor
- Replace default cursor with a **small white dot** + outer ring that expands on hover over interactive elements
- Triangle cursor like tajmirul is cool but a dot+ring is more polished and universally appealing

### 2. Navigation
- **Hamburger icon** (two horizontal lines) fixed top-right
- On click → **right-side drawer overlay** slides in with:
  - **SOCIAL** column: GitHub, LinkedIn, Twitter/X
  - **MENU** column: Home, About, Stack, Experience, Projects (with colored dots like reference)
  - **GET IN TOUCH**: email link at bottom
- Page content shifts/dims behind the drawer

### 3. Hero Section
- **Massive uppercase heading**: "AI" in indigo (#6366f1), "UNDERGRAD" in white — stacked, full-width
- Below: "Hi! I'm **Ahmed Moosani**. A creative AI Undergrad passionate about building intelligent systems, contributing to open source, and exploring machine learning."
- **CTA button**: "HIRE ME" or "VIEW WORK" in filled indigo
- **Right side stats**: "4+ Projects", "500+ Contributions", "3+ Years Coding" — vertically stacked
- **Particle star-field background** — subtle animated dots floating
- Custom colored **scrollbar accent** (indigo instead of green)

### 4. About Section
- Large philosophical quote (full-width, massive font): *"I believe in harnessing AI to solve real-world problems, ensuring every project delivers meaningful impact."*
- Separator: "This is me." text + horizontal line
- **Two-column layout**: "Hi, I'm Ahmed." (bold, left) + two paragraphs describing approach (muted gray, right)
- Text reveals on scroll via GSAP

### 5. Tech Stack Section
- Header: "My Stack"
- **Filter tabs**: AI/ML, Frontend, Backend, Tools
- **Icon grid**: Large icons for Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, React, JavaScript, Docker, Git, Linux, etc.
- Icons fade/stagger in on scroll

### 6. Experience Section
- Header: "My Experience"
- **List layout** (similar to reference): Company name, role, dates — each row with clean separator
- Scroll-triggered reveal

### 7. Selected Projects Section
- Header: "SELECTED PROJECTS"
- **Numbered project list** (like reference): `_01.`, `_02.`, etc.
- Each row: project number + tech tags on top, large project name below
- **Key interaction**: Hovering one project **dims all others** to ~30% opacity — creates a cinematic focus effect
- Projects: DeepFake Detection, Travel Chatbot, Object Recognition, LangChain Chatbot

### 8. Contact / Footer
- "Have a project in mind?"
- Large clickable email: **ahmedmoosani@email.com** (or your real email)
- Footer: "Design & built by Ahmed Moosani" + GitHub link

